a_0=\frac{1}{\pi}\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\sin x\cos{2x}dx=\frac{1}{\pi}\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\frac{1}{2}(\sin{3x}-\sin x) dx=0
a_1=\frac{1}{\pi}\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\sin x\cos{2x}\cos x dx=\frac{1}{\pi}\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}(\sin x\cos x)\cos{2x}dx=\frac{1}{\pi}\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\frac{1}{2}\sin{2x}\cos{2x}dx=
\:\:\:\:\:\:\:\:\:\:\frac{1}{\pi}\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\frac{1}{4}\sin{4x}dx=0
b_1=\frac{1}{\pi}\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\sin x\cos{2x}\sin xdx=\frac{1}{\pi}\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\sin^{2} x\cos{2x}dx=\frac{1}{\pi}\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}\frac{1}{2}(1-\cos{2x})\cos{2x}dx
\sin x \cos 2x = \frac{1}{2} \left( \sin 3x - \sin x \right).
 \sin(a) \cos(b) = \frac{\sin(a+b)+\sin(a-b)}{2} 
